
# Secret scanning (sgim-n25.8): block the commit if gitleaks finds a secret
# in STAGED content. Scoped to `--staged` (not the whole working tree) so
# this stays fast and so gitignored dev files (e.g. /cms/.env) — which can
# never be staged — are never in scope to begin with. Uses `mise exec --`
# rather than a bare `gitleaks` call because the tool is mise-managed and
# may not be on PATH in every shell (e.g. GUI git clients).
mise exec -- gitleaks git --staged --no-banner -c .gitleaks.toml --exit-code 1 .

# Fast pre-commit gate: prettier --write + eslint --fix on STAGED files only,
# scoped per package (see /lint-staged.config.mjs). Whole-project typecheck and
# the full test suite run in `mise run check` / CI, not here — this hook must
# stay fast.
#
# Bypass (discouraged): `git commit --no-verify` skips this hook entirely.
# Reach for it only when you know CI will still catch the issue.
npx lint-staged
